item.title: What number sprite is the main log in screen in noobscape source?
item.dc:creator: @Zach_Knight Zach Knight
item.description:
@Zach_Knight wrote:

The dynamic login screen with the changing background is generated procedurally from landscape n shit, the RuneScape logo on top of that background is entirely dependent on what client you’re using, as there are many versions and not all of them hold this image in the same spot or even have this image in the cache, but I think `da real hype’ is right for most client versions you would be using.

item.dc:creator: @matty_matt matty matt
item.description:
@matty_matt wrote:

[quote=“Wife Beater, post:4, topic:551073”][quote author=matty matt link=topic=669987.msg4480047#msg4480047 date=1428968095]
it is not a sprite
[/quote]

Yes it is you dumb idiot. Its 3150.[/quote]
I thought he was talking about the login box. yes it could be 3150, but to find out for sure go to your mudclient and at the top it should tell you specifically what number your “startlogo” sprite will be. You can then go further to unpack all your sprites files and actually look at them to be 100 percent sure.
@“Wife beater”: I’m that, but your name tells all about your low esteem problems that you have. it’s ok.
